cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.CL 

The paper focuses on deep learning techniques for computer vision tasks such as image retrieval and patch matching. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of attention mechanisms and loss functions, which are common topics in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper involves the use of similarity metrics and datasets related to multimedia, which are relevant to the sub-categories of cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
